text: Autauga County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census the population was 58,805. Its county seat is Prattville. Autauga County is part of the Montgomery Metropolitan Statistical Area. ==Settlements== ===Cities=== *Millbrook (part - some of Millbrook is in Elmore County) *Prattville (part - some of Prattville is in Elmore County) ===Towns=== *Autaugaville *Billingsley ===Unincorporated communities=== *Booth *Jones *Marbury *Pine Level ==Places of interest== Autauga County is home to several parks, such as Wilderness Park, Heritage Park, and Overlook Memorial Park. ==Border counties== *Chilton County, Alabama - north *Elmore County, Alabama - east *Montgomery County, Alabama - southeast *Lowndes County, Alabama - south *Dallas County, Alabama - west ==References== Category:Alabama counties Category:1818 establishments in Alabama Territory
title: Autauga County, Alabama
